<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13104] Controller should notify the RaftClient when it resigns</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13104</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; Throwable handleEventException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name,
                                             Optional&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; startProcessingTimeNs,
                                             Throwable exception) {
          ...
          renounce();
          &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; UnknownServerException(exception);
      }
 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the active controller encounters an event exception it attempts to renounce leadership. Unfortunately, this doesn&apos;t tell the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;RaftClient&lt;/tt&gt; that it should attempt to give up leadership. This will result in inconsistent state with the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;RaftClient&lt;/tt&gt; as leader but with the controller as inactive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should change this implementation so that the active controller asks the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;RaftClient&lt;/tt&gt; to resign. The active controller waits until&#160;&lt;tt&gt;handleLeaderChange&lt;/tt&gt; before calling &lt;tt&gt;renounce()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
